{
  "stem": "21786.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There had been many doctors in the camp, and these were chosen and were selected, I think, by the SS doctors.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Besides Mengele, I remember only Klein.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were no other doctors there, so they were distinguishable-- no, they stayed human beings.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, under the circumstances you worked, then under circumstances where it was done, it-- sometimes it was very difficult to stay that decent human being.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had all kinds of orderlies and nurses-- there was a nursing personnel, as I mentioned.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] then there have been-- there haven't been any kapos, any overseers there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was a-- that was a-- that was, I mean, a lucky stroke for this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were usually in attendance to show themselves off.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The patients, no, were not-- well, they were under-treated, naturally, for we didn't have the medication.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they have not-- nobody was beaten, nobody was, I mean, shot.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Only at one, two occasions there was a selection.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In other words, they took out people who were sick so that they would fill somewhere a quota-- which was missing the quota.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's a kind of tragic to mention it, under the name of quota.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The plan, the general plan, in Birkenau was to gas and cremate 10,000 people a day, which is a harrowing task.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Actually, the gassing was simpler than the burning of the bodies.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The crematoria took only a certain amount of the bodies.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they had to open-- they had to dig open ditches, and staple the body, and burn them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was this smell, tremendous smell, which was permeating all through the compound.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
